    <h2>FAQs About Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips and Gluten</h2>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>1. Are Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips safe for people with celiac disease?</h3>
        <p>Yes, Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips are generally considered safe for people with celiac disease, as they do not contain gluten ingredients and are manufactured in a gluten-free facility. However, always check the packaging for the most current information.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>2. Do Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips have a gluten-free label?</h3>
        <p>No, Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips do not have a gluten-free label, but they are made without gluten-containing ingredients and in a facility that avoids gluten cross-contamination.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>3. Can I use Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips in gluten-free baking?</h3>
        <p>Yes, Kirkland Semi-Sweet Chocolate Chips are a great option for gluten-free baking, as they are free from gluten ingredients and have a low risk of cross-contamination.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq">
        <h3>4. Are there any other gluten-free chocolate chip brands?</h3>
        <p>Yes, brands like Enjoy Life and Pascha offer gluten-free certified chocolate chips, which are also free from other common allergens like dairy and soy.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>

    <div class="conclusion">
